              "text": "To solve \\(17 \\times 19\\), we'll use the distributive property, which allows us to break the problem down into simpler parts. \n\n1. **Break down one of the numbers**: We can express 19 as \\(20 - 1\\).\n   \n2. **Apply the distributive property**:\n   \\[\n   17 \\times 19 = 17 \\times (20 - 1)\n   \\]\n   By applying this, we get:\n   \\[\n   17 \\times 20 - 17 \\times 1\n   \\]\n\n3. **Calculate each part**:\n   - First, calculate \\(17 \\times 20\\):\n     \\[\n     17 \\times 20 = 340\n     \\]\n   - Then, calculate \\(17 \\times 1\\):\n     \\[\n     17 \\times 1 = 17\n     \\]\n\n4. **Combine the results**:\n   Now, subtract the second result from the first:\n   \\[\n   340 - 17 = 323\n   \\]\n\nThus, the final answer is:\n\n\\[\n323\n\\]",
